rows.text: {{fb|British Mandate for Palestine}}{{efn-ua|name=ISR|[[Mandatory Palestine national football team|Mandatory Palestine]] was succeeded by [[Israel national football team|Israel]] from the 1950 qualification.}}

{{fb|EGY|1922}}{{efn-ua|Egypt was later succeeded by the {{fb|UAR}}, a political union between Egypt and Syria, which entered the 1962 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches. Later, Egypt entered the 1966 qualification independently but still under the name "United Arab Republic", but withdrew yet again before playing any matches. The team's first appearance after it changed its name back to Egypt came in 1974.}}

{{fb|JPN|1947}}{{efn-ua|Japan entered the 1938 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}
{{fb|KOR|1949}}

{{fb|CHN}}
{{fb|IDN}}{{efn-ua|Indonesia entered the 1938 qualification as the {{fb|DEI}}, but qualified by walkover due to other teams' withdrawals. It also entered the 1950 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}
{{fb|CYP|1960}}{{efn-ua|Cyprus entered the 1958 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}
{{fb|ECU}}{{efn-ua|Ecuador entered the 1950 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}

{{fb|NGY|name=Dutch Guyana}}{{efn-ua|name=SUR|Dutch Guyana entered the 1938 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches. It was succeeded by Suriname from the 1978 qualification.}}

{{fb|VEN|1954}}{{efn-ua|Venezuela entered the 1958 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}

{{fb|BER}}
{{fb|SLV}}{{efn-ua|El Salvador entered the 1938 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}

{{fb|OMA|1970}}{{efn-ua|Oman entered the 1986 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}
{{fb|PAK}}
{{fb|GAB}}{{efn-ua|Gabon entered the 1966 and 1974 qualifications, but on both occasions withdrew before playing any matches.}}

{{fb|LIB}}{{efn-ua|Lebanon entered but was disqualified during the 1986 qualification, and the team's matches from that campaign were annulled.}}
{{fb|SRI}}{{efn-ua|Sri Lanka entered the 1974 (as {{fb|CEY}}) and 1978 qualifications, but on both occasions withdrew before playing any matches.}}

{{fb|GNB}}
{{fb|RWA|1962}}{{efn-ua|Rwanda entered the 1990 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}

{{fb|MYA|1974}}{{efn-ua|Myanmar entered the 1950 (as {{fb|Burma|1948}}), 1994 and 2002 qualifications, but on all three occasions withdrew before playing any matches.}}
{{fb|TLS}}

{{fb|TUV}}{{efn-ua|Tuvalu was not a member of FIFA at the time of the 2006 qualification and had not entered the FIFA World Cup, although the matches in the football tournament of the South Pacific Games did count towards the qualification tournament for the OFC and Tuvalu's results did count in determining advancement from this stage.}}
{{fb|BHU}}{{efn-ua|Bhutan entered the 2010 qualification, but withdrew before playing any matches.}}
